In a New Year 's message to the Serbian people , <COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">President Vojislav Kostunica</COREF> said the year 2001 will be a time of domestic healing after <COREF ID="0" TYPE="IDENT">the triumph of what <COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">he</COREF> called freedom without violence</COREF> .
<COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">Mr. Kostunica</COREF> was referring to <COREF ID="0" TYPE="IDENT">the popular uprising in October that forced former President Slobodan Milosevic to accept electoral defeat</COREF> .
<COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">Mr. Kostunica</COREF> stressed that legal ways must be found to solve the issue of Montenegro 's drive for independence .
